               <msContents defective="false">
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1" defective="false">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page of Texts I and II, alternating with black lines; elements of musical notation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of punctuation signs and text dividers.&#xD;
Text I:&#xD;
Names of antiphons (mäwaśǝʾt) followed by feast or day names; names of sections of antiphons and their abbreviations (mǝlṭan); the words yǝbarǝkǝwwo, ṣälot and their abbreviations.&#xD;
Text II:&#xD;
Names of sections (wazema); names of antiphons and their abbreviations sometimes followed by the name of the day or part of the day (e.g., maḫǝlet, mäzmur, sälam, ʾabun, ʾaryam, ʾǝsmä lä-ʿaläm, zä-ʾamlakiyä); names of other chants sometimes followed by the name of the day (e.g., mǝlṭan, qǝnnǝwat, ʿǝzl); elements of the Table of halleluiatic chants; names of the categories of melody and their abbreviations (ʿǝzl, gǝʿǝz).</rubric>
                     <incipit defective="false">
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit defective="false">
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note anchored="true"/>
                  </msItem>
