                        <item xml:id="e1">- Fols. 4ra, 191vb: Short ownership notes that state that the book belongs to the church of May ʾAbʾa Maryam.&#xD;
- Fols. 104rb-104vb have been affected by humidity. The text was rewritten in a crude secondary hand.&#xD;
- Erasures: e.g., fols. 28rb, 32rab, 34va, 38rb, 40rb, 51v.&#xD;
- Erasures marked by thin lines: fol. 140rb.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures: e.g., fols. 59va, 106rb, 116rb, 140rb, 147va.&#xD;
- Corrections written above erasures: fols. 30ra, 39rb.&#xD;
- Immediate corrections marked by thin line above and below the word: fols. 35va, 68vb, 122ra.&#xD;
- Omitted passages inserted in the margin: e.g., fols. 8r, 9v, 12v, 15r, 32r.&#xD;
- Tämälläs-sign in the shape of a cross, indicating the place where the omission written in the margin, belong: e.g., fols. 12vb, 15ra, 36va, 57va.&#xD;
- Spaces for rubricated names left unfilled: fols. 189vab, 190rab, 190vab, 191ra.&#xD;
- The first written line is continued into the margin between columns: fol. 49va.&#xD;
- Sign in the shape of a cross with a loop at the end of each arm, written in the margin in red or black ink: e.g., fols. 7v, 13v, 21r, 32r, 48v.&#xD;
- Sign in the shape of two perpendicular lines with a loop at the end of the horizontal arm, written in the margin: fols. 23v, 25v. &#xD;
- The letter ድ written in the margin: fols. 24r, 42v, 43r.&#xD;
- Scribbles and doodles: fols. 1r, 191v, 192r, 192v.</item>
